<subSubSection box="[199,1277,1513,1539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1081,1971]" box="[199,1277,1513,1539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1513,1539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Carapace smooth, with a pronounced concave sinuosity in the posteroventral region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="544" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1081,1971]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1549,1575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544">Description:</emphasis>
Carapace medium, sub-triangular in lateral view. VM with a concave sinuosity in the posteroventral region. Dorsal margin angled in the interior portion that coincides with the greatest height. Rounded anterior and posterior margins, the latter being lower. Greater length in the ventral region, just above the ventral sinuosity. Greater anterodorsal height coinciding with the location of the cardinal angle. LV larger than RV with evident overlaps on the central-ventral margin. In the dorsal view, greatest width in the posterior region. Smooth surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1081,1971]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,1729,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="544">Observations</emphasis>
